The article is a proclamation by President Donald J. Trump on United Nations Day. The proclamation recognizes the United Nations' contributions to peace and security among nations. It emphasizes the United States' commitment to the organization's future and the need for fundamental reforms to address the challenges of the 21st century. The United States has pressed for changes to improve the UN's performance, accountability, and responsiveness. The proclamation also highlights the importance of the UN in addressing global challenges such as nuclear proliferation, humanitarian response, regional conflicts, and human rights abuses. It celebrates the combined efforts of member states and acknowledges the work of peacekeeping and humanitarian missions. President Trump proclaims October 24, 2018, as United Nations Day and urges all states and officials under the flag of the United States to observe it with appropriate ceremonies and activities.